50|$|<b>Goatfishes</b> are {{distributed}} worldwide in tropical, subtropical and temperate waters. <b>Goatfishes</b> {{occur in a}} range of habitats. Most species are associated with the bottom of the littoral, but some species of Upeneus can be deep; for example the goatfish Upeneus davidaromi can be found to depths of 500 m. Tropical <b>goatfishes</b> live in association with coral reefs. Some species, such as the freckled goatfish (Upeneus tragula) enter estuaries and rivers, although not to any great extent.|$|E
50|$|Two {{species of}} <b>{{goatfish}}es,</b> the mimic goatfish Mulloidichthys mimicus and Ayliffe's goatfish Mulloidichthys ayliffe {{have evolved to}} mimic the blue-striped snapper Lutjanus kasmira, with whom they often form schools. These are slow, genetic {{changes that have occurred}} during the evolution of <b>goatfishes</b> over many generations.|$|E
